The Ogun State Property and Investment Corporation has expressed shock over the fire incident that gutted the OPIC Plaza at Ikeja, which claimed several lives while seriously injuring others. In a statement signed by the Special Adviser and Managing Director of the Corporation, Abiodun Fari-Arole, the corporation described the tragic incident as a rude shock. He said preliminary reports attributed the cause of the fire to an LPG tanker that exploded in front of the plaza. Fari-Arole disclosed that three bodies were recovered in addition to two bodies earlier reported, bringing the total number of fatalities to five. He offered condolences to the families of the deceased, adding that those injured were receiving adequate treatment. Fari-Arole commended the efforts of the firemen who promptly responded to the incident and appreciated the efforts of security officials who prevented hoodlums from taking advantage of the event. He cautioned against speculations on the general impact of the incident, advising everyone to wait for the report of the investigation into the fire incident. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com